:::info
Snapshots are backups of the database directory of a polkadot or kusama node. If you start a node for the first time it will start building from start (genesis), which will take a while. If you download an up to date database your node will be running quicker.

The snapshots are available in `--database paritydb` and `--database rocksdb` format (rocksdb is the default) with `--pruning 1000`, which is sufficient for a validator node.
:::

## Download the database

### Paritydb kusama
```bash
wget http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-ksmcc3.lz4
```

### Paritydb polkadot
```bash
wget http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-polkadot.lz4
```

### Rocksdb polkadot
```bash
wget http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/rocksdb-ksmcc3.lz4
```

### Rocksdb polkadot
```bash
wget http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/rocksdb-polkadot.lz4
```

## Install the database directly

Install to `/home/polkadot/.local/share/polkadot/chains/<chain>` or change to your target directory.

### Paritydb kusama
```bash
curl -o - -L http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-ksmcc3.lz4 | lz4 -c -d - | tar -x -C /home/polkadot/.local/share/polkadot/chains/ksmcc3
```

### Paritydb polkadot
```bash
curl -o - -L http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-polkadot.lz4 | lz4 -c -d - | tar -x -C /home/polkadot/.local/share/polkadot/chains/polkadot
```

